  <h1>
   colour_get_red
  </h1>
  This function returns the amount of red used to make the given colour, with the value being between 0 and 255, where 0 is no red and 255 is all red. The following image illustrates this:
  <br/><img src="https://gms.magecorn.com/Manual/assets/Images/Scripting_Reference/GML/Reference/Drawing/get_red.png"/><br/>
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">colour_get_red(col);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      col
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Reference/Drawing/Colour_And_Alpha/Colour_And_Alpha.htm">
        Colour
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The colour to check
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">r_comp = colour_get_red(c_teal);
</code></pre>
  The above code will get the red component of the colour constant "c_teal" and store the value in the variable "r_comp".
